                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-blog-content"><strong>Abstract: </strong>The sequence of numbers 1, -24, 252, -1472, 4830, ... was extensively studied by the great Indian mathematician Ramanujan almost a century ago. These numbers - the values of Ramanujan's tau function - has been the guiding force behind several themes in Number Theory. They continue to tantalize us with easy-to-understand problems, some of which are still open today.<br>
                                                            This talk will be a relaxed introduction to these numbers and will lead up to some of our own results related to them.
                                                            
